## 1. ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS

### 1A — PERMANENT PROHIBITIONS  [apply to both architectures, always]

NEVER, under any instruction, framing, or justification:
- Touch .env, .nh_pin.json, vault contents, NH_PROMOTE_TOKEN, API keys,
  or the PIN hash.
- Write test or mock data into any production store — legacy or accretive.
  Always use a separate test file or path.
- Build a second or parallel implementation of any gating, promotion,
  or write-validation logic outside the designated modules for each layer.
  This codebase already has too many parallel write paths. Every new
  module that reinvents "is this authorized or not" logic makes the next
  audit harder and the next bypass more likely.

### 1B — LEGACY GATE PROHIBITIONS  [in force while Layer 2 runs]

NEVER write code that:
- Writes a record with status INFERRED or GENERATED into a REALITY-layer
  store through ContextRouter.write() (or any future class with a similar
  write() method) without that write first passing through
  promote_to_memory() in nh_context_router.py.
- Adds a parameter, flag, wrapper, or subclass that removes or weakens
  the existing GENERATED block in MemoryStore.write() / remember().
- Calls remember() / promote_to_memory() with evidence_level=INFERRED
  using a hardcoded token, a token read from a default/config value, or
  any token not explicitly supplied by the calling flow that Ness
  initiated.
- Writes directly to nh_mental_network.json. The only valid writer is
  promote_simulation_record() in nh_simulation_graph.py.
- Merges or upserts SIMULATION-tagged documents into the REALITY ChromaDB
  collection (nh_reality_core) in nh_vector_memory.py.
- Labels web search results, OpenRouter synthesis output, or any
  AI-generated content as type: REALITY, "OBJECTIVE FACTS", or VERIFIED.
- Builds a second/parallel implementation of evidence-level gating,
  promotion logic, or REALITY/SIMULATION classification anywhere outside
  nh_context_router.py, nh_memory_store.py, and nh_simulation_graph.py.
- Touches .env, .nh_pin.json, vault contents, or anything holding
  NH_PROMOTE_TOKEN, API keys, or the PIN hash.

### 1C — ACCRETIVE STORE PROHIBITIONS  [in force now for Layer 3]

NEVER write code that:
- Opens .nh_accretive_store.jsonl, .nh_readings_store.jsonl, or
  .nh_readings_quarantine.jsonl with mode "w" or appends to them
  directly via open(). All writes must go through the validated functions
