## 2A. THE LEGACY GATE  [in force for Layer 2 — old-stack writes only]

There is exactly one authorized path from unverified content into REALITY
for the legacy gate stack:

    promote_to_memory()  —  nh_context_router.py
        ├─ GENERATED       → always blocked, no override possible
        ├─ INFERRED        → requires NH_PROMOTE_TOKEN or explicit
        │                     user_confirmed=True from Ness
        ├─ VERIFIED        → written directly
        └─ REPORTED_SPEECH → written directly, but requires non-empty
                               speaker AND quote fields

Nothing else is authorized to put a non-VERIFIED record into a REALITY
store. In particular:

ContextRouter.write() is NOT a gate by itself. It only blocks
(a) SIMULATION-layer records written without _internal=True, and
(b) REALITY-layer records with status UNKNOWN. It does not check evidence
level, does not require a token, and WILL write an INFERRED or GENERATED
record straight into .nh_reality_store.jsonl if called directly.

This is not theoretical — it is the exact bug found in the June 19 2026
audit. nh_epistemic_sandbox.py's route_result() built a
reality_record(status=INFERRED, ...) for any thought scored as "SIGNAL"
and called _router.write(rl_rec) directly, skipping promote_to_memory()
entirely. The record went straight into REALITY with no token, no review,
no human approval — exactly the bypass this whole architecture exists to
prevent.

Rule going forward: if you are about to write a _router.write(record)
call where record.layer == REALITY and record.status != VERIFIED,
stop. Route it through promote_to_memory() instead.

This rule governs any code that writes to the old-stack stores or calls
old-stack gate functions. It remains in force until the legacy gate is
explicitly decommissioned by Ness.


## 2B. THE ACCRETIVE STORE GATE  [in force for Layer 3]

The sovereignty boundary for the accretive architecture is
nh_accretive_store.py. There is no status-label gate in this layer.
The boundary is enforced by the module's own validated functions:

    append_root()       → blocked while .nh_roots.sealed exists;
                          schema-validates the 7-field root record;
                          atomic append only.

    append_reading()    → calls _validate_reading() first (shape gate);
                          verifies each id in `reads` exists in sealed
                          roots before commit; checks idempotency_key;
                          routes to quarantine or production path based
                          on the path argument supplied.
                          DECIDED FUTURE BEHAVIOR (not yet implemented):
                          production path must additionally require
                          .nh_readings_production_authorized to exist,
                          and must fail closed if absent. This gate
                          requires a separately approved code change to
                          nh_accretive_store.py before it enforces it.

    _validate_reading() → gates on shape only; rejects malformed records;
                          never rejects uncertain or low-confidence
                          readings; never gates on meaning content.

Nothing may write to .nh_accretive_store.jsonl or any readings store
except through these functions. Direct file writes, even well-formed
ones, are prohibited.


